1 bunch broccolini
½ lemon
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
1 packet chicken breast strips
1 packet Roasted Potatoes with Garlic Herb Butter
1 packet Smokey Aioli
Olive Oil

• Trim baby broccoli. Slice lemon
into wedges
• Heat a large frying pan over mediumhigh heat. Cook baby broccoli and a
good dash of water until tender,
5 mins
• Add spinach and a squeeze of lemon
juice, then stir until wilted.
• Transfer to a plate

• Meanwhile, combine spice blend and
a drizzle of olive oil in a bowl. Add
chicken and toss to coat.
• Return frying pan to a high heat
with oil
• Cook chicken until cooked through,
3-4 mins each side

• While chicken is cooking, pierce a
few holes in potato packet, then
microwave until hot and steaming,
3 mins
• Plate up the chicken, greens and
potatoes
• Serve with smokey aioli and any
remaining lemon wedges